SPECIAL DAY/WEEK/MONTH: Recognizes April 21, 2026, as Wholesalers Day at the
state capitol
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To recognize Tuesday, April 21, 2026, as Wholesalers Day at the state capitol and to
3 commend the Louisiana Association of Wholesalers for its contributions to the
4 economy and citizens of Louisiana.
5 WHEREAS, wholesalers play a critical role in Louisiana's economy by serving as
6 the vital link between manufacturers and retailers and ensuring the efficient distribution of
7 goods across the state; and
8 WHEREAS, the Louisiana Association of Wholesalers represents a diverse network
9 of businesses that support local economies, create jobs, and contribute significantly to the
10 state's economic growth and stability; and
11 WHEREAS, members of the Louisiana Association of Wholesalers are committed
12 to maintaining high standards of service, professionalism, and integrity while supporting
13 Louisiana's businesses and communities; and
14 WHEREAS, wholesalers help ensure that essential goods, including food, beverages,
15 medical supplies, and other necessities are delivered safely and reliably to communities
16 throughout Louisiana; and
17 WHEREAS, Wholesalers Day at the state capitol provides an opportunity to
18 recognize the hard work and dedication of those in the wholesale industry and to highlight
19 their importance to the state's continued prosperity, and it is fitting to recognize the
20 Louisiana Association of Wholesalers for its valuable contributions.
